	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: SMB2J Palette Question</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Shanem wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It worked, how did you do that in FCEUX (as I also wanted to change the green to the Koopa Troopas in castle stages)?</div><br /><br />It is actually a simple thing, if you use the PPU viewer, the Palette Display values are under the Character Display.<br /><br />Palettes are one of the simplest thing to hack ever, really!<br /><br />EDIT: Koopas are 1C 36 17 in both castle and underground levels.<br /><br />Here are what they mean<br /><br />1C = Dark Cyan<br />36 = Light Peach<br />17 = Brown

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


