		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Shanem wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">From what I see FCEUX does not have this feature, any more suggestions?</div><br /><br />Look under Debug &gt; PPU Viewer, Contains both Character and Palette viewers,<br /><br />Then, Look for values via your HEX editor (excluding color 0 of any palette slot, they are transparent!)<br /><br />EDIT: What you originally did is change the .pal data (64 colors of the NES palette), What you want is the above ROM hacking method!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


